726874f-b.title: Queens: Hoffman Drive - 58th Avenue
726874f-b.text:
Hoffman Drive, south side, between Fifty-eighth and Fifty-
ninth Avenues, showing in three views tho Rohirson house. This
house stands on or near the site of the Quaker Meeting House
which was erected in 1722 and sold in 1760. Adjoinig the house
Nas a burial ground. The house which was used as a dvelling from
1760 was consumed by fire in 1844. The owners of the present
house were Robert kack, 18527; J. Robinson, 1850; Rohirson, 1891;
and possibly Mrs. Howard in 1873.
July 1923.
View 2: Februarv 1924.
Viev 3: March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
